name: Allied with the Twins
flavor: The battlements bristled with spears and swords and scorpions, there was an archer at every crenel and arrowslit, the drawbridge was up, the portcullis down, the gates closed and barred.
text: Attached character gets +10 STR while defending.

name: Frozen Solid
text:
Attach to an attachment or location.
Treat attached attachment or location as though its text box were blank.

name: Northman's Grit
text: Attached character gets +3 STR and is immune to events.
flavor: "Bronze and iron are stronger than gold and silver" -Robb Stark

name: Arya Stark
text: Stealth. Deadly. Response: after you win a challenge, put Arya Stark into play from your hand.
flavor: "Who is going to say that she isn't Arya Stark?" -Jaime Lannister

name: Catelyn Stark
text: Immune to character abilities. Response: after Catelyn Stark is killed, choose a [stark] character in your dead pile. Then, put that character into play. [doomed]
flavor: "You bloody bastards cut her throat too deep for that. But she remembers."

name: Eddard Stark
text: Deadly. Renown. Response: after a [stark] character is killed, stand Eddard Stark. [doomed]
flavor: "No," Eddard said with sadness in his voice. "Now it ends."

name: Jojen Reed
text: Marshalling: kneel Jojen Reed and kneel 1 influence to name a card. Then, discard the top 3 cards of a player's deck. For each copy of the named card discarded, Jojen Reed claims a power.

name: Meera Reed
text: House Stark only. Stealth. Any phase: kneel 2 influence to put Meera Reed into play from your hand. Any Phase: kneel 1 influence to return Meera Reed to her owner's hand.

name: Shaggydog
text: No attachments. Deadly. While you control at least 1 [stark] Lord character, Shaggydog gets +3 STR and is immune to events.
flavor: The darkness sprang at him, snarling.

name: ∞ Northern Heir
text: Northern Heir does not kneel to defend. Dominance: kneel 3 influence to return Northern Heir from your dead pile to play.

name: Greatjon's Elite
text: No attachments. Deadly.
flavor: "Your attack must be so fiece that the Ironborn hav no leisure to wonder if anyone is creeping down on them from the north." -Robb Stark

name: House Stark Herald
text: Lower the cost for you to play <Army> characters by 1.
flavor: As the neared the Twins, Robb donned his crown and summoned Catelyn and Edmure to ride beside him.

name: Huntress in the Swamp
text: Stealth.
flavor: "There are ways through the Neck that are not on any map, Uncle. Ways known only to the crannogmen." -Robb Stark

name: Keeper of the New Gods
text: Any phase: kneel Keeper of the New Gods to choose a character. Until the end of the phase, that character gets +2 STR.

name: Lookout
text: While Lookout is attacking, Army characters may not defend.
flavor: Catelyn's father's guards waited on the water stair with her brother.

name: Last Hearth's Finest
text:
No attachments. Deadly.
While there is at least one doomed card in any dead pile, Last Hearth's Finest does not kneel to attack.

name: The Iron Throne
text: Response: after a carde is placed into any player's dead pile, kneel The Iron Throne to reveal up to the top 2 cards of your deck, if able. Put any one character with cost 2 or lower thus revealed into play, and put the remaining cards on th ebottom of your deck in any order.

name: Winterfell Castle
text: Deathbound. Response: after you win a challenge as defender, each opponent must choose and kill a character he or she controls. [doomed]
flavor: Somewhere in the great stone maze of Winterfell, a wolf howled.

name: Broken Tower
text: Deathbound. Marshalling: kneel Broken Tower to lower the cost of the next [stark] card you play this phase by 1. [doomed]

name: Northern Fiefdoms
text: Limited. Marshalling: kneel Northern Fiefdoms to lower the cost of the next [stark] card you play this phase by 1. +1 influence

name: Winterfell Barracks
text: Challenges: discard Winterfell Barracks from play (cannot be saved) to search your deck for a character and put that character into play. At the end of the phase, return that character to its owner's hand.

name: Gutter Rat's Cunning
text: Attached character gets +2 STR and gains stealth.
flavor: "Where's a gutter rat like Lumpyhead get him a sword?" -Lommy

name: Tywin's Protégé
text: Attached character gets +2 STR. Response: after you win a challenge during which attached character participated, choose an attachment. Return that attachment to its owner's hand.

name: Cersei Lannister
text: Response: kneel Cersei Lannister and kneel 1 influence to cancel the effects of a character ability. Then, that character's controller must choose and discard a card from his or her hand. [doomed]
flavor: And it is not like her to choose a catspaw who would make such a royal botch of the killing.

name: Ser Jaime Lannister
text:
Deadly.
Immune to opponent's character abilities.
[doomed]
flavor: "Believe what you will. I'm past caring what people say of me."

name: Tommen Baratheon
text: Response: after a character is killed, kneel 1 influence to have Tommen Baratheon claim 1 power (limit 3 per phase).
flavor: There was only one way Tommen would become king.

name: Tyrion Lannister
text: Stealth. While Tyrion Lannister is participating in a challenge, he gains "Challenges: kneel 2 influence to change the current challenge to an [intrigue] challenge."

name: Tywin Lannister
text: Response: cancel the effects of an event card unless any player kneels 1 influence. [doomed]
flavor: "I owe you nothing."

name: ∞ Western Heir
text: Stealth. Dominance: kneel 3 influence to return Western Heir from your dead pile to play.

name: Enemy Informer
text: Response: after you play Enemy Informer from your hand, choose and kneel a character.
flavor: "Is everyone someone's informer in this cursed city?" -Eddard Stark

name: Expendable Ally
text: Response: discard Expendable Ally from play (cannot be saved) to cancel the effects of a character or location ability.
flavor: That's all it will take, and our noble allies will be at one another's throats.

name: Highgarden Reinforcements
text: No attachments. Deadly. Response: after you play Highgarden Reinforcements from your hand, draw 2 cards.
flavor: The golden rose of Highgarden was seen everywhere.

name: Joffrey's Herald
text: Any Phase: kneel Joffrey's Herald and kneel 2 influence to choose a character or location. Until the end of the phase, that character or location gains a House affiliation of your choice.

name: Littlefinger's Collectors
text: You may pay a +1 gold penalty (cannot be ignored) while playing Littlefinger's Collectors from your hand. Response: after you pay Littlefinger's Collectors with a gold penalty, each opponent chooses and discards 2 cards from his or her hand, if able.

name: Ser Armory's Poachers
text: While there is at least one doomed card in any dead pile, Ser Amory's Poachers gains stealth and renown.

name: Courtesan of Highgarden
flavor: "Our little rose has a good many ladies waiting in attendance on her, night and day." They stood behind her now, almost a dozen of them. -Lady Cersei Lannister

name: Casterly Rock
text: Deathbound. Challenges: kneel Casterly Rock to choose a character. Until the end of the phase, choose one of the following: that character gets -2 STR, that character loses an [intrigue] icon, or that character loses stealth and renown. [doomed]

name: The Iron Throne
text: Response: after a card is placed into any player's dead pile, kneel The Iron Throne to discard the top 3 cards of each opponent's deck.

name: Corrupt Treasury
text: Deathbound. Marshalling: kneel Corrupt Treasury to lower the cost of the next [lannister] card you play this phase by 1. [doomed]

name: Halls of the Red Keep
text: During [intrigue] challenges, raise the Claim value on each player's revealed plot card by 1.
flavor: The stones have ears in the Red Keep

name: Tywin's Manse
text: Response: after you win dominance, claim 1 power for your House.

name: Western Fiefdoms
text: Limited. Marshalling: kneel Western Fiefdoms to lower the cost of the next [lannister] card you play this phase by 1. +1 influence

name: Chosen by R'hllor
text: Attached character gets +2 STR. Response: after a player claims power for his or her House, stand attached character.
flavor:
"R'hllor chooses queerly, then."
-Stannis Baratheon

name: Stormlander's Pride
text: Attached character gets +2 STR and gains "Any phase: kneel 3 influence to stand this character."
flavor: "Humble?" Catelyn supplied. Renly laughed. "You must allow a king some flaws, my lady."

name: Melisandre
text: Deadly. Response: after a character claims power for renown, Melisandre claims 1 power. [doomed]
flavor: "Is it me your fear? Or what we do?"

name: Renly Baratheon
text:
While any other character has renown, Renly Baratheon gains renown.
While any other character has stealth, Renly Baratheon gains stealth.

name: Robert Baratheon
text: Renown. Response: after Robert Baratheon is killed, move all power from all characters to your House card. [doomed]
flavor: "Robert was the true steel." -Donal Noye

name: Selyse Baratheon
text: Any phase: discard 1 power from a character you control to choose and stand a character you control (limit 3 per round).
flavor: With prominent ears, a sharp nose, and the faintest hint of a mustache on her upper lip.

name: Ser Cortnay Penrose
text: Ser Cortnay Penrose gets +1 STR for each [baratheon] character in any dead pile.
flavor: "May the Others bugger your Lord of Light"

name: ∞ Stormland Heir
text: Renown. Dominance: kneel 3 influence to return Stormland Heir from your dead pile to play.

name: Braavosi Spy
text: Marshalling: kneel Braavosi Spy to choose a non-Limited location. Until the end of the phase, treat that location as though its text box were blank.

name: Converted Maester
text: Response: after you play Converted Maester from your hand, choose a card in any dead pile. Move that card to its owner's discard pile.

name: Mother of Shadows
text: While there is at least one doomed card in any dead pile, Mother of Shadows is immune to opponents' events and character abilities.

name: Pentoshi Captain
text: You may pay a +1 gold penalty (cannot be ignored) while playing Pentoshi Captain from your hand. Response: after you play Pentoshi Captain with a gold penalty, move all power from a character to Pentoshi Captain.

name: Ser Axell's Elite
text: No attachments. Deadly.

name: Knight Commander
text: Knight Commander gets +1 STR while you control an Army character.

name: Student of the Stars
flavor: Cressen had never seen a comet half so bright, nor yet that color, that terrible color, the color of blood and flame and sunsets.

name: Storm's End
text: Deathbound. Challenges: kneel Storm's End and kneel 1 influence to choose and stand 2 characters. [doomed]
flavor: Yet Storm;s End endured, through centuries and tens of centuries, a castle like no other.

name: The Iron Throne
text: Response: after a card is placed into any player's dead pile, kneel The Iron Throne to choose and discard a non-unique attachment from play.

name: Aegon's Sept
text: Challenges: discard Aegon's Sept from play (cannot be saved) to return a card with printed cost X or lower from your discard pile to your hand. X is the number of characters participating in the challenge.

name: Crumbling Stone Dragon
text: Deathbound. Marshalling: kneel Crumbling Stone Dragon to lower the cost of the next [baratheon] card you play this phase by 1. [doomed]

name: Obsidian Ramparts
text: Response: after a character claims power for renown, look at up to the top 2 cards of your deck. Then, put any number of those cards on the bottom of your deck and return the to the top of your deck in any order.

name: Stormlands Fiefdoms
text: Limited. Marshalling: kneel Stormlands Fiefdoms to lower the cost of the next [baratheon] card you play this phase by 1. +1 influence

name: Ironborn's Strength
text: Attached character gets +4 STR.
flavor: "We are the Ironborn, and once we were conquerors. Our writ ran everywhere the sound of waves was heard." -Euron Greyjoy

name: Aeron Damphair
text: Immune to character abilities. Any phase: kneel Aeron Damphair and kneel 2 influence to discard up to 2 power from a character or House card.
flavor: Aeron Damphair was a prophet. He did not suffer petty lords ordering him about like some thrall.

name: Euron Crow's Eye
text:
Immune to events.
While Euron Crow's Eye is standing, [greyjoy] characters you control gain stealth.
flavor: Only one living kraken has never known defeat. Only one has never bent his knee.

name: Gormond Goodbrother
text: Response: after Gormond Goodbrother is killed, claim 2 power for your House.
flavor: Three tall sons had been born to Goodbrother's wife, and it was said that no man could tell one son from the others.

name: Theon Greyjoy
text: Stealth. Theon Greyjoy does not kneel to attack or defend while you control at least 1 Warship location. [doomed]
flavor: Let Theon be born again from the sea.

name: Victarion Greyjoy
text: Immune to events. Challenges: kneel 2 influence to put into play a Warship location from your hand.
flavor: "Lord Captain of the Iron Fleet, and a fearsome warrior."

name: ∞ Island Heir
text: Response: after Island Heir is declared as an attacker, choose and stand a Warship. Dominance: kneel 3 influence to return Island Heir form your dead pile to play.

name: Bannermen to the Kraken
text: No attachments. Deadly. Response: after you win an unopposed challenge in which Bannermen of the Kraken is participating, it claims 2 power.

name: Deadly Axeman
text: While there is at least one doomed card in any dead pile, Deadly Axeman gets +3 STR.
flavor: "And I say all of Westeros is dying. Those who follow me will feast to the end of their days." -Euron Crow's Eye

name: Sea Raiders
text: Limited. No attachments.
flavor: "You are to harry the Stony Shore, raiding the fishing villages and sinking any ships you chance to meet." -Lord Balon Greyjoy

name: Prophet of the Waves
text: Any phase: kneel Prophet of the Waves to choose a location. Until the end of the phase, that location gains Deathbound.
flavor: "The sea is never weary. I must be as tireless" -Aeron Damphair

name: Rider through the Storm
flavor: He was not fond of horses, but necessity required that he ride. A storm was brewing, he could hear it in the waves.

name: Vanguard Axeman
text: Response: discard Vanguard Axeman from play (cannot be saved) to cancel the effects of an event.
flavor: "That is not the Old Way. Ironmen fight with swords and axes, not by flinging rocks."

name: Longship "Black Wind"
text: Deathbound. Response: kneel Longship "Black Wind" and kneel X influence to cancel the effects of an event with influence cost X or lower. [doomed]

name: Longship "Great Kraken"
text: Deathbound. Challenges: kneel Longship "Great Kraken" to choose a character. Until the end of the phase, that character gets +4 STR. [doomed]

name: Longship "Silence"
text: Deathbound. Response: after you win an unopposed challenge, kneel Longship "Silence" to choose a character. That character claims 2 power. [doomed]

name: The Iron Throne
text: Response: after a card is placed into any player's dead pile, kneel The Iron Throne to choose a character. Until the end of the phase, that character cannot be killed.

name: Blazewater Coast
text: Response: after a character is saved, discard the top 2 cards from any player's deck.
flavor: "Rise." he told the spluttering boy. " You have drowned and been returned to us."

name: Coastal Tower
text: Deathbound. Marshalling: kneel Coastal Tower to lower the cost of the next [greyjoy] card you play this phase by 1. [doomed]

name: Iron Island Fiefdoms
text: Limited. Marshalling: kneel Iron Island Fiefdoms to lower the cost of the next [greyjoy] card you play this phase by 1. +1 influence

name: Ten Towers Battlements
text: Challenges: kneel Ten Towers Battlements to choose 2 characters. Until the end of the phase, switch those characters' printed STR.
flavor: Ten Towers was airier, more comfortable, better sited than ancient Harlaw Hall.

name: Ruler of Meereen
text: While attached character has more attachments than any other character, it gets +1 STR, gains renown, and cannot be killed.

name: Daenerys Targaryen
text: Characters you control get +1 STR.
flavor: Daenerys did not flinch or cry out. She liked the heat. It made her feel clean.

name: Drogon
text: No attachments. Deadly. Challenges: kneel 1 influence to attach Drogon to a character (counts as Condition attachment with the text "Attached character gets -5 STR.") Any phase: kneel 1 influence to return Drogon to its owner's hand. [doomed]

name: Khal Drogo
text: Deadly. While Khal Drogo is participating in a challenge, he gains: "Challenges: kneel 3 influence to choose and discard a defending character (cannot be saved.)" [doomed]

name: Rhaegal
text: No attachments. Deadly. Challenges: kneel 1 influence to attach Rhaegal to a character (counts as a Condition attachment with the text "Attached character cannot be killed.") Any phase: kneel 1 influence to return Rhaegal to its owner's hand. [doomed]

name: Ser Jorah Mormont
text: Immune to character abilities. Response: after Ser Jorah Mormont comes into play, choose and discard an attachment from an opponent's character.

name: Viserion
text: No attachments. Deadly. Challenges: kneel 1 influence to attach Viserion to a character (counts as a Condition attachment with the text "Attached character gets +3 STR and gains stealth, renown and deadly.") Any Phase: kneel 1 influence to return Viserion to its owner's hand. [doomed]

name: Viserys Targaryen
text:
Visery Targaryen cannot be saved.
After a character comes into play, Viserys Targaryen claims 1 power.
When Viserys Targaryen has 4 or more power, he is discarded from play.

name: ∞ Lesser Ko
text: Lesser Ko's STR cannot be lowered. Dominance: kneel 3 influence to return Lesser Ko from your dead pile to play.
flavor: "There are a dozen new khalasars on the Dothraki Sea, where once there was only Drogo's." -Ser Jorah Mormont

name: Free Cities Trader
text: Free Cities Trader gets +2 STR for each attachment on it.
flavor: "A trader from Qarth once told me that dragons came from the moon." -Doreah

name: Half-Trained Youth
text: Response: after you win a challenge, kneel Half-Trained Youth to choose a character without attachments. Until the end of the phase, that character gets -1 STR and is killed if its STR is 0.

name: Eastern Mercenary
text: Eastern Mercenary gains stealth while it has at least 1 attachment.

name: Upstart Slave
text: While there is at least one doomed card in any dead pile, Upstart Slave gets +3 STR.
flavor: "You are foolish strawhead slave." Irri said.

name: Warlock's Servitors
text: Immune to character abilities. Deadly
flavor: "Why do men lower their voices when they speak of the warlocks of Qarth?"

name: Great Pyramid of Meereen
text:
Deathbound.
Each opponent is considered to have 1 additional doomed character in his or her dead pile.
[doomed]
flavor: In the plaza before the Great Pyramid, the Meereenese huddled forlorn.

name: The Iron Throne
text: Response: after a card is placed into any player's dead pile, kneel The Iron Throne to return a [targaryen] attachment from your discard pile to your hand.

name: Dothraki Sea
text: Dominance: kneel Dothraki Sea to choose a character without attachments. Until the end of the phase, that character gets -1 STR and is killed if its STR is 0.

name: Eastern Feifdoms
text: Limited. Marshalling: kneel Eastern Fiefdoms to lower the cost of the next [targaryen] card you play this phase by 1. +1 influence

name: Ghiscari Outpost
text: Deathbound. Marshalling: kneel Ghiscari Outpost to lower the cost of the next [targaryen] card you play this phase by 1. [doomed]

name: Plaza of Punishment
text: Challenges: discard Plaza of Punishment from play (cannot be saved) to choose an attacking or defending character without attachments. Until the end of the phase, that character gets -3 STR and is killed if its STR is 0.

name: Xaro's Home
text: Response: after you play an attachment from your hand, kneel 1 influence to draw a card.
flavor: She had expected a palace. She had not expected a palace larger than many a market town.

name: Dornishman's Flourish
text: Attached character gets +1 STR and gains renown.
flavor: Their armor was heavily enameled and inlaid with burnished copper, shining silver, and soft red gold.

name: Deadly Seduction
text: After plot cards are revealed, discard attached character from play.

name: Areo Hotah
text:
Deadly.
Areo Hotah's STR cannot be lowered.
flavor: He keeps that great axe razor sharp, even sleeps with it beside him.

name: Arianne Martell
text: Stealth. Response: after a character with stealth is declared as an attacker, stand Arianne Martell. [doomed]
flavor: She was the sort of woman who despised weakness.

name: Ellaria Sand
text: Response: after you lose a challenge, move 1 power from any character to Ellaria Sand.
flavor: "And this is Ellaria Sand, mine own paramour." -Oberyn Martell

name: The Red Viper
text: Renown. Response: after a character is killed or discarded from play, kneel 1 influence to stand The Red Viper. Then, it claims 2 power. [doomed]
flavor: I have hungered for a long time. Though not for food.

name: ∞ Southron Heiress
text: Southron Heiress cannot be bypassed by characters with stealth. Dominance: kneel 3 influence to return Southron Heiress from your dead pile to play.

name: Arianne's Admirer
text: You may play an additional Limited card each round.

name: Dornish Lancer
text: Stealth. Resposne: after Dornish Lancer bypasses a character using stealth, draw a card.

name: Initiate of Poisons
text: Any phase: kneel 1 influence to choose a character. Until the end of the phase, that character loses an [intrigue] icon.

name: Lord Edric's Knight
text: Stealth.
flavor: The salty Dornishmen were lithe and dark, with smooth olive skin and long black hair streaming in the wind.

name: Prince's Spy
text: Response: after an opponent draws cards during the draw phase, look at those cards.

name: House Messenger
text: After you play House Messenger from your hand, reveal the top 2 cards of your deck to all players. Then, put one of those cards into your hand, and the other on the bottom of your deck.

name: Student of Subtlety
text: Any phase: kneel 2 influence to choose a character. Until the end of the phase, that character gains or loses an icon of your choice.
flavor: He had studied at the Citadel, going so far as to forge six links of a maester's chain.

name: Warmonger
text: While there is at least one doomed card in any dead pile, Warmonger gets +1 STR for each character in each player's dead pile.
flavor: "You head my small folk in the streets, crying out for me to call my spears."

name: Sunspear
text:
Deathbound.
An opponent cannot initiate a challenge against you if he or she has won a challenge against you by 4 or more that phase.
[doomed]
flavor: "Perhaps you will return to Sunspear with me when the day's bloodletting is done."

name: The Iron Throne
text: Response: after a card is placed into any player's dead pile, kneel The Iron Throne to put the topmost event of your discard pile on top of your deck.

name: Desert Cache
text: Deathbound. Marshalling: kneel Desert Cache to lower the cost of the next [martell] card you play this phase by 1. [doomed]

name: Doran's Palanquin
text: +4 influence

name: Dornish Fiefdoms
text: Limited. Marshalling: kneel Dornish Fiefdoms to lower the cost of the next [martell] card you play this phase by 1. +1 influence

name: Ruins in the Sand
text: Response: after you lose a challenge, discard Ruins in the Sand from play (cannot be saved) to give all characters you control +2 STR until the end of the phase.
flavor: "Ours is a harsh, poor land, yet not without its beauties"

name: King-Beyond-the-Wall
text: Wildling character only. Response: after you win a challenge, kneel attached character to choose a non-Wildling character. Discard all attachments and power from that character.

name: Born to Kill
text: Attached character gets +1 STR and gains a [military] icon.
flavor: "Does it give you joy to scare people?" "No, it gives me joy to kill people."

name: Paper Money
text: Attach to your House card. Marshalling: kneel attached House card to lower the cost of the next character you play this phase by X. X is the number of attachments on your House card.

name: Raised to Lie
text: Attached character gets +1 STR and gains an [intrigue] icon.
flavor: "I never asked you to lie for me." "I never did." she said. "I left out part, is all."

name: Risen to Power
text: Attached character gets +1 STR and gains a [power] icon.
flavor: She has broken him, as a man breaks a horse. She would ride him to power if she could, and for that she gave my sons to the fire.

name: Valyrian Steel Spear
text: Attached character gains deadly.

name: Benjen Stark
text: No attachments. Stealth. Response: after Benjen Stark is killed, kneel 2 influence to exchange a plot card in your used pile with a plot card in your plot deck. [doomed]

name: Jon Snow
text: No attachments. Deadly. Response: kill another Night's Watch character (cannot be saved) to save Jon Snow from being killed or discarded.

name: Jaqen H'ghar
text: Stealth. Deadly. Response: after a character is saved, kneel 2 influence to choose and kill a different character with equal or lower STR.

name: Lord of Bones
text: Immune to character abilities. Any phase: kneel 2 influence to choose a non-Limited location. Until the end of the phase, treat that location as though its text box were blank.

name: Mag the Mighty
text: Deadly. Challenges: kneel 1 influence to choose a Wildling character. Until the end of the phase, that character gets +1 STR.

name: Mance Rayder
text: You may choose to pay a +2 gold penalty (cannot be ignored) when you play a Wildling character. Response: after you play a Wildling character with a gold penalty, choose and discard from play a non-Limited location with cost 3 or lower. [doomed]

name: Pypar
text: No attachments. While any player has an Others plot card revealed, Pypar gains "Response: after you win a challenge in which Pypar participated, draw 3 cards."

name: Ygritte
text: Response: after you play Ygritte from your hand, choose a Night's Watch character. Take control of that character.
flavor: "You know nothing, Jon Snow."

name: Janos Slynt
text: Stealth. Any phase: give a Night's Watch character an [intrigue] icon until the end of the phase. Limit once per phase.
flavor: "Janos, if you mean that I ought to tell your brothers to choose you, have the courage to say so." -Stannis Baratheon

name: Fallen Brother
text: After you play Fallen Brother from your hand, kneel 1 influence or choose and discard from play a Night's Watch or Wildling character.

name: Mammoth Rampager
text:
No attachments. Deadly.
After you play Mammoth Rampager from your hand, each player must choose and discard a character in play.

name: Roving Pillagers
text: You may choose to pay a +1 gold penalty (cannot be ignored) when you play Roving Pillagers. Response: after you play Roving Pillagers with a gold penalty, choose and discard from play a non-Limited location.

name: Ruthless Defender
text: No attachments. While any player has an Others plot card has his or her revealed plot card, Ruthless Defender gets +1 STR and gains a [intrigue] and [power] icon.

name: Student of Coin
text: After you reveal a plot card, draw a card.
flavor: "The master of coin must be frugal." -Varys

name: Veteran Builder
text: No attachments. You may choose to pay a +1 gold penalty (cannot be ignored) when you play Veteran Builder. Response: after you play Veteran Builder with a gold penalty, it claims 2 power.

name: War Giant
text: No attachments. Deadly. Response: after you win a challenge and count 8 or more total STR, stand all Wildling characters.

name: War Mammoth
text: No attachments. Deadly. Response: after you win a challenge in which War Mammoth participated and count 8 or more total STR, search your deck for a card named War Mammoth or War Giant, and put it into play.

name: Wildling Emissary
text: Response: after you win a [power] challenge in which Wildling Emissary participated, discard Wildling Emissary from play (cannot be saved) to choose and discard from play a location with printed cost 3 or lower.

name: Wildling Messenger
text: Reponse: after you win an [intrigue] challenge in which Wildling Messenger participated, discard Wildling Messenger from play (cannot be saved) to draw 3 cards.

name: Wildling Scout
text: Response: after you win a [military] challenge in which Wildling Scout participated, discard Wildling Scout from play (cannot be saved) to choose and kill a character with STR 3 or lower.

name: Harrenhal
text: Dominance: kneel Harrenhal and kneel 3 influence to choose and kill a character.
flavor: Every child of the Trident knew the tales told of Harrenhal.

name: The Wall
text: Deathbound. Dominance: kneel 2 influence and discard one of your Night's Watch character from play (cannot be saved) to choose and discard a character from play. [doomed]
flavor: The wall is more than just ice and stone.

name: Blackwater Rush
text: +2 influence

name: Bloody Trident
text: After a player loses an unopposed challenge, discard 2 power from that player's House.

name: Crossroads
text:
+1 income
+1 influence

name: Fallow Fields
text:
Limited.
+2 income
+2 influence

name: King's Landing
text: Deathbound. Any phase: kneel 1 influence to choose a House. All characters with that House affiliation get +1 STR until the end of the phase. [doomed]

name: Minor Fiefdom
text: +1 influence

name: Ravaged Coast
text: After a player loses an unopposed challenge, he or she must choose and kneel a standing location he or she controls, if able.

name: Robert's Deathbed
text:
After you kneel Robert's Deathbed to pay an influence cost, discard it from play (cannot be saved).
+3 influence

name: The New Gift
text: Deathbound. Marshalling: kneel The New Gift to lower the cost of the next attachment you play this phase by 1. You may pay any amount of that attachment's gold cost using influence instead. [doomed]

name: The Old Gift
text: Deathbound. Marshalling: kneel The Old Gift to lower the cost of the next location you play this phase by 1. You may pay any amount of that location's gold cost using influence instead. [doomed]

name: Dorne Goes to War
text: House Martell only. Deathbound. Dominance: kneel 4 influence and discard your hand to reveal the top 7 cards of your deck to all players, then put them into your hand. [doomed]

name: Field of Fire
text: House targaryen only. Deathbound. Challenges: kneel 3 influence to kill all defending characters. [doomed]

name: From the Ashes of Winterfell
text: House Stark only. Deathbound. Dominance: kneel 4 influence to search your deck for up to 3 copies of a character or location with the same title, reveal those cards to all players, and put them into your hand. Then shuffle your deck. [doomed]

name: Hands of Gold are Always Cold
text: House Lannister only. Deathbound. Response: kneel 3 influence to cancel the "when revealed" effect of a plot card. [doomed]

name: Plea to R'hllor
text: House Baratheon only. Deathbound. Dominance: kneel 4 influence to put all non-doomed characters from all dead piles into play. [doomed]

name: Sound the Horn of Dragons
text: House Greyjoy only. Deathbound. Dominance: kneel 4 influence to discard all locations from play (cannot be saved). [doomed]
flavor: "With this horn, ironmen, I can bind dragons to my will." -Euron Crow's Eye

name: ∞ Forever Burning
text: House Targaryen only. Deathbound. Any phase: choose a character. Until the end of the phase, that character gets -1 STR. Dominance: kneel 1 influence to return Forever Burning from your dead pile to your hand.

name: ∞ Forever Faithful
text: House Baratheon only. Deathbound. Challenges: choose and stand a character with STR 3 or lower. Dominance: kneel 1 influence to return Forever Faithful from your dead pile to your hand.

name: ∞ Forever Listening
text: Deathbound. Marshalling: each player with 4 or fewer cards in hand draws a card. Dominance: kneel 1 influence to return Forever Listening from your dead pile to your hand.

name: ∞ Forever Plundering
text: House Greyjoy only. Deathbound. Marshalling: choose a character. Until the end of the phase, that character cannot be saved. Dominance: kneel 1 influence to return Forever Plundering from your dead pile to your hand.

name: ∞ Forever Scheming
text: House Martell only. Deathbound. Any phase: choose and stand an influence providing location. Dominance: kneel 1 influence to return Forever Scheming from your dead pile to your hand.

name: ∞ Forever Stalwart
text: House Stark only. Deathbound. Response: after you win a challenge as defender, claim 1 power for your House. Dominance: kneel 1 influence to return Forever Stalwart from your dead pile to your hand.

name: ∞ Forever Whispering
text: House Lannister only. Deathbound. Any phase: choose a character. Discard 1 power from that character. Dominance: kneel 1 influence to return Forever Whispering from your dead pile to your hand.

name: A Lord's Ransom
text: House Lannister only. Any phase: kneel 2 influence to cancel a triggered effect that would kill a character you control. Until the end of the phase, that effect's controller cannot trigger any further effects or abilities.

name: Along the Saltspear
text: House Greyjoy only. Challenges: kneel X influence to choose X Warship locations. Until the end of the phase, those locations become characters with 2 STR, stealth, and a [military] and [power] icon.

name: Arianne's Rejection
text: House Martell only. Dominance: choose and kneel a House card. Then, discard all attachments on that House card.

name: Arrest and Imprison
text: House Lannister only. Deathbound. Response: kneel 1 influence to cancel the effects of a character or location ability. Then, kneel that character or location. [doomed]

name: Arya's Revenge
text: House Stark only. Deathbound. Any phase: kneel 3 influence to choose and kill a character. [doomed]

name: ∞ Shadow in the North
text: Challenges: kneel a character with STR 2 or lower. Response: after an Others plot card is revealed, kneel 1 influence to return Shadow in the North from your discard pile to your hand.

name: Blood Magic
text: House Targaryen only. Deathbound. Any phase: kneel X influence to choose a character without attachments. Until the end of the phase, that character gets -X STR and is killed if its STR is 0. [doomed]

name: Bound by R'hllor
text: House Baratheon only. Marshalling: kneel 2 influence to look at each opponent's hand. Then, choose and discard an attachment or non-unique character with printed cost 2 or lower from each of those hands.

name: I am King Here!
text: Challenges: choose an attacking or defending [baratheon] character. Until the end of the phase, that character gets +2 STR. If you win the challenge, claim 2 power for your House.

name: Injurious Poison
text: House Martell only. Deathbound. Response: copy the effects of an event card or character ability just triggered (without paying any costs). [doomed]

name: Insidious Ways
text: Challenges: choose an attacking [lannister] character. Until the end of the phase, that character gets +2 STR. If you win the challenge, draw 2 cards.

name: Jojen's Counsel
text: Challenges: choose a [stark] character. Until the end of the phase, that character gets +3 STR and does not kneel to defend.

name: Like the Seas
text: Challenges: choose an attacking or defending [greyjoy] character. Until the end of the phase, that character gets +2 STR and cannot be killed.

name: Love is Poison
text: House Lannister only. Challenges: kneel X influence to choose X characters. Those characters must participate in the next challenge this phase, if able.

name: Make an Example
text: Response: after you win a challenge and count 8 or more total STR, claim 3 power for your House. Limit 1 per phase.

name: New Khalassar
text: House Targaryen only. Response: after a Dothraki character is killed, kneel 3 influence to have each other Dothraki character claim 1 power.

name: Night favors the Silent
text: Challenges: choose an attacking [martell] character. Until the end of the phase, that character gains stealth. If you win the challenge, shuffle any one player's discard pile into his or her deck.

name: Nightmares
text: Any phase: choose a character or location. Until the end of the phase, treat the text box of that character or location as though it were blank.

name: Only Your Life
text: House Targaryen only. Dominance: kneel 1 influence to exchange any character in your dead pile with a character in your hand.
flavor: She told herself she would die for him, if she must.

name: Please Let It Burn
text: Challenges: during a challenge, choose an opponent. Lower the claim value on his or her revealed plot card by 1 for the duration of the challenge.

name: Purge the Traitors
text: Dominance: kneel 2 influence to discard from play (cannot be saved) all unique characters and locations controlled by more than one player.

name: Retreat to Dragonstone
text: House Baratheon only. Any phase: kneel 3 influence to discard all attachments from play.

name: Salt in your Eyes
text: House Greyjoy only. Response: kneel 1 influence to cancel the effects of an event card just played.
flavor: The salt made his eyes burn, until it was all he could do not to cry out.

name: Seek out the Traitors
text: Dominance: kneel X influence to choose and discard from play X Ally, Mercenary or Bastard characters.

name: Shadow Play
text: House Baratheon only. Deathbound. Challenges: kneel 2 influence to choose a character with STR 3 or lower. Until the end of the phase, take control of that character. [doomed]

name: Spinning Slash
text: Challenges: choose an attacking [targaryen] character. Until the end of the phase, that character gets +2 STR. If you win the challenge, choose and discard an attachment from play.

name: Tempting Fate
text: Dominance: kneel 3 influence to discard the top 5 cards from each opponent's deck. Draw a card for each doomed card discarded in this way.

name: The Hand's Judgment
text: House Stark only. Challenges: choose an opponent. That opponent cannot trigger any effect or abilities during [military] and [power] challenges this phase.

name: The scorpion's Sting
text: House Martell only. Challenges: kneel 2 influence to choose a character. Until the end of the phase, that character loses all of its printed icons. Then, for each icon lost, that character's controller must choose and discard a card from his or her hand.

name: Tidal Wave
text: House Greyjoy only. Deathbound. Any phase: kneel 2 influence to choose and discard a location from play (cannot be saved). [doomed]

name: Too Baseborn to Matter
text: Any phase: choose a character without a [power] icon. Discard all attachments and power from that character.
flavor: Law and custom gave the baseborn few rights.

name: Too Blind to See
text: Challenges: choose a character without an [intrigue] icon. Until the end of the phase, that character cannot be declared as an attacker or defender.

name: Too Weak to Fight
text: Any phase: choose a character without a [military] icon. Until the end of the phase, that character gets -3 STR.

name: Vengeance for Eddard
text: House Stark only. Any phase: kneel 2 influence to search your deck for a [stark] character with printed cost 2 or lower and put it into play.

name: Westeros Bleeds
text: Dominance: kneel 4 influenceto discard all characters from play.
flavor: When the old king was still alive, he'd not have stood for this. "King Robert?" Arya asked, forgetting herself. "King Aerys, gods grace him." the old man said.

name: A Beggared Realm
text: Each opponent adds 1 to his or her total income.

name: Benjen's Cache
text: When revealed, if you have 1 or fewer Kingdom plot cards in your used pile, search your deck for a card and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Blue Eyes, Black Skin
text: When revealed, if you have 2 or more Others plot cards in your used pile, choose and kill a character

name: Break Their Defense
text: You cannot claim power for unopposed challenges.

name: Called by the Gods
text: When revealed, if you have 1 or fewer Kingdom plot cards in your used pile, search your deck for a character, reveal that character, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Catch Them Unprepared
text: Players with a lower total initiative than you cannot declare more than 1 defender during a challenge.

name: Clash of Kings
text: Characters you control do not kneel to attack or defend during [power] challenges.

name: Dark and Full of Terrors
text: When revealed, choose and kneel X characters and/or locations. X is the number of Others plot cards in your used pile.

name: Fortified Position
text: Treat all characters in play as though their text boxes were blank (except for Traits).

name: Fire and Blood
text:
House Targaryen only.
When revealed, you may choose a character you control. Return that character to its owner's hand.

name: Foe I was Born to Fight
text: Opponents with Others plot cards as their revealed plot card cannot declare defenders this phase.

name: For Love of Duty
text: Character you control get +1 STR.

name: Found by Providence
text: When revealed, if you have 1 or fewer Kingdom plot cards in your used pile, search your deck for a location card, reveal it to all players, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Game of Thrones
text: Characters you control do not kneel to attack or defend during [intrigue] challenges.

name: Hear Me Roar
text:
House Lannister only.
Characters without an [intrigue] icon get -1 STR.

name: Ours is the Fury
text:
House Baratheon only.
When revealed, choose a character in any discard pile, Move that character to it's owner's dead pile.

name: Outmaneuver
text: When revealed, cancel the effects of each opponent's revealed plot card. Each opponent must then reveal a new plot card.

name: Safe Within the Walls
text: Characters cannot be killed.

name: Storm of Swords
text: Characters you control do not kneel to attack or defend [military] challenges.

name: Superior Numbers
text: You cannot play non-character cards and cannot trigger card effects or abilities.

name: The Gathering Storm
text: When revealed, each opponent may return his or her revealed plot card to his or her plot deck and reveal a new plot card.

name: The Wraiths Appear
text: Characters get -2 STR.

name: Unbowed, Unbent, Unbroken
text:
House Martell only.
Characters you control cannot be bypassed with stealth.

name: We Do Not Sow
text:
House Greyjoy only.
Each challenge you win by 4 or more total STR is considered unopposed.

name: Whose Name May Not Be Spoken
text: When revealed, name attachment or location. Each player must choose and discard one of his cards of the named type from play, if able.

name: Wildling Siege
text: Increase the cost for all players to play characters and attachments by 2. This is considered to be a gold penalty.

name: Winter has Come
text: When revealed, if you have 2 or more Others cards in your used pile, kill all characters (cannot be saved).

name: Winter is Coming
text:
House Stark only.
Add +2 to your total STR for each challenge in which you have at least 2 participating character.
